            <h2>Theoretical Framework</h2>
            <div class="bords"></div>
            <p class="txt-style2">
                The Umang model has been conceptualised with a strategic interplay of women empowerment & leadership
                frameworks and socio-behavioural theories of change.
            </p>
            <p>
                It relies on <a href="javascript:void(0)"
                                class="modal-open">
                    Naila
                    Kabeer’s
                </a>
                <a href="https://www.files.ethz.ch/isn/28994/dp108.pdf" target="_blank">
                    <span class="highlights">Empowerment Model</span>
                </a> that
                offers a three-dimensional conceptual approach for women empowerment encompassing Resources (as part
                of
                the preconditions of empowerment), Agency (as an aspect of process) and Achievement (as a measure of
                outcomes). Kabeer defines empowerment as the process by which those who have been denied the ability
                to
                make choices acquire such an ability.
            </p>
